{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"fields":{"description":"# Ship a client-usable AGENTS.md template + a drift-guard test\n\n## Why\n\nTeams that ADOPT rebar in their own repos need to teach their agents how to drive rebar (the\nticket workflow, claim/gates, MCP tool set, idea/linking/tags/session-logs) WITHOUT inheriting\nrebar's internal dev specifics (Gerrit split-remote, module-size, Serena, our exact landing\nflow). A single copyable, provider-neutral template gives them that — and because `AGENTS.md`\nis read by every major harness, one file serves all their agents. A test keeps the template\nfrom drifting away from the authoritative rebar-usage docs, exactly as\n`tests/unit/test_skill_shared_sync.py` guards the skills' shared/ file today.\n\n## What\n\nAdd `templates/AGENTS.md` containing the portable \"how to drive rebar\" guidance, sourced from\nthe authoritative usage docs, with clearly-marked placeholders for the client's own build/test\ncommands and landing flow (e.g. `<!-- CLIENT: your build/test commands -->`). Include NO\nrebar-internal Gerrit/module-size/Serena content. Add a drift-guard test (e.g.\n`tests/unit/test_client_template_sync.py`) that fails if the template's rebar-usage sections\ndiverge from the authoritative source, wired into `make test`. Document the template's purpose\nand copy-usage in a short header comment.\n\n## Scope\n\nIn: `templates/AGENTS.md`, one new test, and a one-line mention in the docs index. Out:\nscaffolding it via `rebar init` (explicitly deferred — a shipped file was chosen over CLI\ncodegen). Depends on: the re-home story (the portable rebar-usage content must be settled).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `templates/AGENTS.md` exists, is provider-neutral, contains rebar-usage guidance plus\n  clearly-marked client placeholders, and contains no rebar-internal Gerrit/module-size/Serena\n  guidance.\n  - Proving: `test -f templates/AGENTS.md`; `rg -c 'Gerrit|module-size|Serena' templates/AGENTS.md` == 0.\n- [ ] A drift-guard test fails when the template diverges from its authoritative source and\n  passes when in sync; it runs under `make test`.\n  - Proving: `make test` green; deliberately editing the template makes the test fail (shown in\n    the change description).\n- [ ] The docs index references the template so adopters can find it.\n\n## De-risking results (drift-guard mechanism resolved)\n\nThe existing `tests/unit/test_skill_shared_sync.py` compares **whole files** byte-for-byte\n(`_identical`, plus a `test_divergence_is_detected` self-check). That pattern does NOT fit the\ntemplate, which is intentionally NOT byte-identical to any doc (it carries client placeholders +\ndifferent framing). **Resolved design: sync a DELIMITED REGION, not the whole file.** Keep the\ncanonical portable rebar-usage prose in ONE source (natural candidate: `docs/ticket-model.md`\nplus the workflow loop authored in S1, or a dedicated `docs/_shared/rebar-usage.md`); embed it\nin `templates/AGENTS.md` between `<!-- BEGIN rebar-usage (generated; do not edit) -->` /\n`<!-- END rebar-usage -->`; the new test asserts that delimited block is byte-identical to the\ncanonical source (mirroring `_identical` + a divergence self-check). Client placeholders\n(build/test/landing) live OUTSIDE the delimited block.\n\nRevised Acceptance Criteria:\n- [ ] The drift-guard test compares the DELIMITED rebar-usage region (not the whole file) and\n  fails when it diverges from the canonical source; a self-test proves divergence is detected.\n  - Proving: `make test` green; perturbing the delimited block makes the test fail.\n- [ ] Client placeholders sit outside the delimited block and carry no rebar-internal content."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784232650082161001,"uuid":"ff51f1f1-5228-49cb-970d-54cd99df7134"}